  "text": "The aim of this study is to characterize the chromosomes of the species M. luteus and M. fauroti, analyzing standard stained mitotic and meiotic cells, in order to begin an effort to establish karyotypic relationships among species in the Pholcidae. Gonads were dissected in Ringers solution for insects, transferred to colchicine solution (0.16% in Ringer for insects) and left for 2 hrs.; a volume of hypotonic solution (tap water) equal to that of the colchicine solution was added and after 15 mins. the material was placed in Carnoy I fixative solution for 60 min., after which it was macerated in 60% acetic acid on the surface of the slide. The slide was dried on a metal heating plate (35-40 ЊC) and stained with a 3% Giemsa solution for 13-15 min. The cells were photographed under a Zeiss microscope and the chromosome morphology classification was determined according to [CITATION_1] . The number of analyzed chromosomal spreads was 65 for M. luteus and 40 for M. fauroti. In each of these spreads, the chromosome number was determined and no intraspecific variation was detected.",
